init_text:
Should Schools Provide Free Pads and Tampons?

Have you ever experienced period shaming, or “period poverty”? Should schools step in to help? Should schools be required to provide free pads and tampons to students? How are pads and tampons similar to toilet paper, soap, Band-Aids and other products that are already provided in schools? How are they different?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: budgeting for products like pads and tampons is different from budgeting for toilet paper, soap and other products.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They are tied to things such as puberty and fertility.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: That makes them a sensitive issue, especially among students.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I believe that parents should supply students with period products.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Period products are not expensive for women and it is a personal issue.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: As a product some people may also be sensitive to it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the fundamentals of their reproductive cycle.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Schools should not have to be held responsible for a product that is so sensitive.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I believe this is an issue solely for parents and their children.
